name: Mature cell length
scoring: The cell length of fully elongated cells (mature-cell length) was measured in the cortex tissue layer
to_definition: "An assay to determine the variation in the length of the plant cell due to cell growth and elongation." [GR:pj]
uo_definition: "A length unit which is equal to one millionth of a meter or 10^[-6] m." [NIST:NIST]

name: Meristem zone length
scoring: The size of the meristem was measured from the quiescent center to the onset of the rapid longitudinal cell expansion in the cortex tissue (meristem zone length)
to_definition: "An assay to determine the variation in the length of the plant cell due to cell growth and elongation." [GR:pj]
uo_definition: "A length unit which is equal to one millionth of a meter or 10^[-6] m." [NIST:NIST]
